      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## ***5. Hypothesis Testing***"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "g-ATYxFrGrvw"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Based on your chart experiments, define three hypothetical statements from the dataset. In the next three questions, perform hypothesis testing to obtain final conclusion about the statements through your code and statistical testing."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Yfr_Vlr8HBkt"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Answer Here."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "-7MS06SUHkB-"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Hypothetical Statement - 1"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "8yEUt7NnHlrM"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "#### 1. State Your research hypothesis as a null hypothesis and alternate hypothesis."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "tEA2Xm5dHt1r"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Hypothesis 1: Agent Shift Affects CSAT Score\n",
        "\n",
        "H₀ (Null Hypothesis): There is no significant difference in CSAT scores between different agent shifts.\n",
        "\n",
        "H₁ (Alternative Hypothesis): There is a significant difference in CSAT scores between agent shifts."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "eTtxMU9GhOE7"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "#### 2. Perform an appropriate statistical test."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "I79__PHVH19G"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Perform Statistical Test to obtain P-Value\n",
        "from scipy.stats import ttest_ind\n",
        "\n",
        "# Separate CSAT scores by shift\n",
        "csat_day = df[df['Agent Shift'] == df['Agent Shift'].unique()[0]]['CSAT Score']\n",
        "csat_night = df[df['Agent Shift'] == df['Agent Shift'].unique()[1]]['CSAT Score']\n",
        "\n",
        "# Perform t-test\n",
        "t_stat, p_val = ttest_ind(csat_day, csat_night, equal_var=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"T-test for Shift vs CSAT:\")\n",
        "print(\"t-statistic:\", t_stat)\n",
        "print(\"p-value:\", p_val)\n",
        "\n",
        "if p_val < 0.05:\n",
        "    print(\" Conclusion: Statistically significant difference in CSAT between shifts.\")\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print(\" Conclusion: No significant difference in CSAT between shifts.\")\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "oZrfquKtyian"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##### Which statistical test have you done to obtain P-Value?"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Ou-I18pAyIpj"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "We performed a Two-Sample Independent t-test (Welch's t-test) using scipy.stats.ttest_ind.\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "s2U0kk00ygSB"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##### Why did you choose the specific statistical test?"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "fF3858GYyt-u"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "This test is appropriate because we are comparing the means of CSAT scores between two independent groups — Day Shift and Night Shift agents. We used equal_var=False to handle unequal variances, making it a Welch’s t-test, which is robust and commonly used when group variances may differ."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "HO4K0gP5y3B4"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Hypothetical Statement - 2"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "4_0_7-oCpUZd"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "#### 1. State Your research hypothesis as a null hypothesis and alternate hypothesis."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "hwyV_J3ipUZe"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Hypothesis 2: Item Price Affects Customer Satisfaction\n",
        "\n",
        "H₀ (Null Hypothesis): Item price has no effect on CSAT scores.\n",
        "\n",
        "H₁ (Alternative Hypothesis): Item price has a significant effect on CSAT scores."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "FnpLGJ-4pUZe"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "#### 2. Perform an appropriate statistical test."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "3yB-zSqbpUZe"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Perform Statistical Test to obtain P-Value\n",
        "# Create high and low price groups\n",
        "high_price = df[df['Item_price'] > 5000]['CSAT Score']\n",
        "low_price = df[df['Item_price'] <= 5000]['CSAT Score']\n",
        "\n",
        "# Perform t-test\n",
        "t_stat, p_val = ttest_ind(high_price, low_price, equal_var=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nT-test for Item Price vs CSAT:\")\n",
        "print(\"t-statistic:\", t_stat)\n",
        "print(\"p-value:\", p_val)\n",
        "\n",
        "if p_val < 0.05:\n",
        "    print(\"Conclusion: Significant difference in CSAT between high- and low-priced items.\")\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print(\"Conclusion: No significant difference in CSAT based on item price.\")\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "sWxdNTXNpUZe"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##### Which statistical test have you done to obtain P-Value?"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "dEUvejAfpUZe"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "We performed a Two-Sample Independent t-test (Welch’s t-test) using scipy.stats.ttest_ind."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "oLDrPz7HpUZf"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##### Why did you choose the specific statistical test?"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Fd15vwWVpUZf"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "This test is used to compare the average CSAT scores between two independent groups — customers who purchased high-priced items (> ₹5000) and those who purchased low-priced items (≤ ₹5000).\n",
        "We used equal_var=False to account for potential differences in variance between the two groups, making it a Welch’s t-test, which is suitable for real-world data with unequal sample sizes or variances."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "4xOGYyiBpUZf"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Hypothetical Statement - 3"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "bn_IUdTipZyH"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "#### 1. State Your research hypothesis as a null hypothesis and alternate hypothesis."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "49K5P_iCpZyH"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Hypothesis 3: Product Category Influences CSAT\n",
        "\n",
        "H₀ (Null Hypothesis): Different product categories have no impact on CSAT scores.\n",
        "\n",
        "H₁ (Alternative Hypothesis): Product categories do affect CSAT score"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7gWI5rT9pZyH"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "#### 2. Perform an appropriate statistical test."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Nff-vKELpZyI"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Perform Statistical Test to obtain P-Value\n",
        "from scipy.stats import f_oneway\n",
        "\n",
        "# Extract CSAT scores by each unique category\n",
        "grouped_scores = [group['CSAT Score'].values for _, group in df.groupby('category')]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Perform ANOVA\n",
        "f_stat, p_val = f_oneway(*grouped_scores)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nANOVA Test for Issue Category vs CSAT:\")\n",
        "print(\"F-statistic:\", f_stat)\n",
        "print(\"p-value:\", p_val)\n",
        "\n",
        "if p_val < 0.05:\n",
        "    print(\" Conclusion: CSAT scores significantly differ across categories.\")\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print(\" Conclusion: No significant variation in CSAT across categories.\")\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "s6AnJQjtpZyI"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##### Which statistical test have you done to obtain P-Value?"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kLW572S8pZyI"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "We performed a One-Way ANOVA (Analysis of Variance) test using scipy.stats.f_oneway.\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ytWJ8v15pZyI"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##### Why did you choose the specific statistical test?"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "dWbDXHzopZyI"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "ANOVA is appropriate here because we are comparing the means of CSAT scores across more than two independent groups — specifically, the different issue categories in the category column.\n",
        "Unlike a t-test (which compares two groups), One-Way ANOVA allows us to determine if at least one category's mean CSAT score differs significantly from the others.\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "M99G98V6pZyI"
      }
    },
