      "source": [
        "#### What all missing value imputation techniques have you used and why did you use those techniques?"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7wuGOrhz0itI"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##Missing Value Imputation Techniques Used:\n",
        "1.Median Imputation (Numerical Columns):\n",
        "Used because it's robust to outliers and preserves the central value of skewed data like Item_price.\n",
        "\n",
        "2.Mode Imputation (Categorical Columns):\n",
        "Used to fill missing categories with the most frequent value, ensuring minimal distortion of distribution.\n",
        "\n",
        "3.Dropped Columns with >40% Missing Values:\n",
        "Because they lack sufficient data for reliable imputation and could negatively affect model quality."
