      "source": [
        "### 4. Feature Manipulation & Selection"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "-oLEiFgy-5Pf"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "#### 1. Feature Manipulation"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "C74aWNz2AliB"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Manipulate Features to minimize feature correlation and create new features\n",
        "# Step 1: Get correlation matrix (numeric only)\n",
        "corr_matrix = df.corr(numeric_only=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 2: Identify highly correlated pairs\n",
        "threshold = 0.85  # You can adjust this\n",
        "upper = corr_matrix.where(np.triu(np.ones(corr_matrix.shape), k=1).astype(bool))\n",
        "to_drop = [column for column in upper.columns if any(upper[column] > threshold)]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 3: Drop those columns\n",
        "df.drop(columns=to_drop, inplace=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Optional: print what was dropped\n",
        "print(\"Dropped due to high correlation:\", to_drop)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "h1qC4yhBApWC"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "#### 2. Feature Selection"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "2DejudWSA-a0"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Select your features wisely to avoid overfitting\n",
        "from sklearn.feature_selection import VarianceThreshold, mutual_info_classif\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "\n",
        "# Separate features and target\n",
        "X = df.drop(columns=['CSAT Score'])\n",
        "y = df['CSAT Score']\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Remove low variance features\n",
        "X = pd.DataFrame(VarianceThreshold(threshold=0.01).fit_transform(X),\n",
        "                 columns=X.columns[VarianceThreshold(threshold=0.01).fit(X).get_support()])\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Select top 15 features using Mutual Information\n",
        "mi = mutual_info_classif(X, y)\n",
        "mi_df = pd.DataFrame({'Feature': X.columns, 'MI Score': mi})\n",
        "top_features = mi_df.sort_values(by='MI Score', ascending=False)['Feature'].head(15).tolist()\n",
        "X = X[top_features]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Selected top 15 features:\\n\", top_features)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "YLhe8UmaBCEE"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "##### What all feature selection methods have you used  and why?"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "pEMng2IbBLp7"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "I used:\n",
        "\n",
        "1.Variance Threshold – to remove features with very low variance, which don’t contribute meaningful information to the model.\n",
        "\n",
        "2.Mutual Information (MI) – to rank features based on how much information they provide about the target (CSAT Score), selecting the top 15 features to reduce overfitting.\n",
        "\n",
        "These methods help keep only relevant features and improve model performance."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "rb2Lh6Z8BgGs"
      }
    },
